    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The **Principle of Least Privilege** means granting users and systems only the minimum access necessary to perform their specific jobs, nothing more. In a real business scenario, you would assign new employees a single, limited account with access solely to the tools they need for daily tasks, rather than giving them the same high-level credentials as the CEO. Over time, you regularly audit these permissions to revoke any rights that are no longer required, preventing unauthorized access to sensitive data or systems if an employee's account is compromised.",
