      "content": "Network admins can enforce these rules by implementing Role-Based Access Control (RBAC), which automatically assigns permissions based on job functions rather than individual users. They also rely on automated tools to continuously monitor access logs and immediately revoke any sudden spikes in unauthorized privilege elevation. Additionally, enforcing the \"justification approval process\" for new access requests helps prevent managers from casually handing out excessive permissions without a documented business need.",
